[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Well, this is turning into a busy week. SeaDance 2.0 has released, kind of. There\'s a lot to unpack in the details, and we\'re going to go over all of that, but we are headed in a good direction. Also, Luma Labs has dropped a new'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'thinking image model. This one looks really cool, but when you pair it with another recent Luma update, well, that\'s where things get pretty powerful. Then you pair that with SeaDance 2.0, well, you\'re in for a wild ride.'

[00:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Kicking off, ByteDance have released SeaDance 2.0 globally, although they do have a very narrow definition of what globally means. Look, the whole SeaDance saga has been kind of a dramatic roller'

[00:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'coaster. Originally, it was set for release in late February, which got pushed to March, which then got pushed to mid-March, and then lawsuits and C&amp;Ds got involved, and well, I mean, now we\'re here. Along the way, there were'

[00:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'all kinds of rumors ranging from like heavy nerfing of the model to outright cancellation. We\'ve had some janky and questionable workarounds via API calls, and look, I\'m going to be honest, that that part\'s not going anywhere. So,'

[01:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'backstory lore complete, SeaDance 2.0 is now available both on CapCut and Dreamina. Although, as of this video, it has only been released to a select number of countries. I know, I know. We\'ll talk about how all this plays out'

[01:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'in just a minute, but yeah, for right now, it is available both on CapCut and Dreamina to users in Indonesia, the Philippines, Thailand, Vietnam, Malaysia, Brazil, and Mexico. And as they note, with expansion over time.'

[01:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Now, why those particular countries? I mean, I presume it\'s threading the needle over the IP issue. These are countries where it can be released while they shore up more protections. In the meantime, they actually have released'

[01:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'some new guardrails, including restricting certain capabilities, uh videos containing real faces. We\'re going to talk about that in a minute, cuz I I don\'t think that\'s as bad as everyone thinks it is. Uh they\'ve also, you know, put in some technology to block unauthorized generation of'

[01:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'intellectual property, so no more Pokémon for you. And they have also implemented C2PA content credentials. This is the invisible watermark that is generated alongside videos that indicate that it is AI generated. Both VEO and'

[02:08] [scene:talk]
